    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sport that evolved during the late 19th and early 20th centuries in the mountainous terrain of the Alps in central Europe. Modern Alpine skiing is competitive, divided into speed events (downhill skiing and the supergiant slalom, or super-G) and technical events (slalom and giant slalom). </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
